Fish1.desc_line1: It's not a snack, and it certainly doesn't smile back... for copyright reasons!

Fish2.desc_line1: The branding on the soda can must have gotten washed off by some kind of liquidy, wavey substance. Oh, right.

Fish3.desc_line1: Don't let it sting you, unless you're into getting tinkled on by random beach-goers.

Fish4.desc_line1: The result of putting Blood and Leech into a bad pokemon generator.

Fish5.desc_line1: Wow! Tapping on it's ribs really does make a xylophone noise!

Fish6.desc_line1: It's not actually made of sand, not even in this universe.

Fish7.desc_line1: Watch out for that stinger! It's called a 'stinger', but it will leave more of a deathy feeling than a stinging one.

Fish8.desc_line1: The tentacles writhe around as it plots it's next move toward bringing an end to this plane of existence.

Fish9.desc_line1: Scaled and icy, this coldblooded predator often travels out of the briney Seasalt shores to the Deepwater Docks to prey on Sand Sharks...

Fish10.desc_line1: This gooey creature evolved from a common ancestor of the Dedotated Ram, hence the curled shell horns.

Fish11.desc_line1: Woah momma thats a big shrimp...

Fish12.desc_line1: Astonishingly, despite its unthreatening exterior of cauliflower and bread, this creature sits atop the food chain according to leading IdleOn Oceanographers. At least, based on currently explored seas...

Bug1.desc_line1: I don't know whyyyy she swallowed a flyyy, perhaps she'll cry from being perpetually made fun of in the form of a nursey rhyme just because she made one bad decision... er, die!

Bug2.desc_line1: Butter Fly? Get it??? Sorry... I promise I wont make this kind of joke again

Bug3.desc_line1: Honestly, I was shocked too at first when I learned that cereal in real life was harvested from Cereal Bugs. Seriously, look it up! Most cereal before 1960 were made from harvested Cereal Bug Nests!

Bug4.desc_line1: Hahaha I had my fingers crossed!

Bug5.desc_line1: I'm so tired of all these blood sucking vermin in IdleOn... and these mosquisnow bugs are annoying too!

Bug6.desc_line1: Ok these bugs are really not making any sense anymore.

Bug7.desc_line1: It's a bee and it's working. As per the Worker Bee Union Act of 35e4, I am barred from making any pun or joke about them.

Bug8.desc_line1: It glows with the joy of a being that knows it's not real, but continues to exist anyway.

Bug9.desc_line1: Amazingly, these bugs have adapted around being static images with no animation, and are able to fly without moving their wings!

Bug10.desc_line1: Wait, is this actually just a piece of dust? I mean it's classified as a bug but like, I mean... the classifiers must get it wrong sometimes right?

Critter1.desc_line1: The living embodiment of the classic cryptocurrency 'Frogecoin'. Very ribbit, much green, wow!!

Critter1A.desc_line1: Ew, it's the living embodiment of that scam alt-coin crypto ripoff, 'Frogecoin Cash'

Critter2.desc_line1: Argg, yer spendin' all me money!

Critter2A.desc_line1: Argghgg, yershpend inall memuh knee!!... Yea, mutants can't speak very well, probably on account of the radiation poisioning and all that.

Critter3.desc_line1: This cutie will stab its way into your heart if you aren't careful! No seriosuly, be careful, the bugger pricked my foot the other day and it hurt bad.

Critter3A.desc_line1: This chrome coloured scorpion came straight from the future! Fuuuutuuuuureee! FUUTUUURREE!!! SOMEONE DIRECT ME TO THE CAN OPENERRRR!!!!

Critter4.desc_line1: Adorable!!! Look how cute it's tail is, and that itty bitty nose, and the fact that it's a mouse and not a rat so I don't want to hit it with a broom!

Critter4A.desc_line1: This mole ain't got no fur! Ew, gross!! Disgusting even!!! What kind of wretched abomination has skin but no thick layer of fur??

Critter5.desc_line1: Hoot hoot! Yea thats all I got for this one.

Critter5A.desc_line1: It's a more expensive hoot, I guess. I ain't got no jokes for owls, they're too cool.

Critter6.desc_line1: It's basically just Gunter but with RTX off.

Critter6A.displayName: Eternal Lord of  The Undying Ember
Critter6A.desc_line1: Bow before the destroyer of all that lies outside his domain, the ruler of the 8th dimension and all that it's flame encompasses, the bringer of light to the blind, and darkness to those who recite his title in full. ...ah crap.

Critter7.desc_line1: It could use a carrot, the lil' guy needs some food!

Critter7A.desc_line2: But I like this one more.

Critter8.desc_line1: You lean closer to the critter, and hear it say 'Dodo tshh do dodo tss dodo tss badabada dodoooo'. So no, that name isn't a typo.

Critter8A.desc_line1: Oh I guess this one is a scarab, not a beetle. You can tell because of the way it is.

Critter9A.desc_line1: One of the only beings strong enough to take on the Eternal Lord of the Undying Ember realm. Their battle would be legendary.

Critter10A.desc_line1: Yo bro I ain't touchin' that thing ain't no way!

Soul1.desc_line1: The soul moans ooOOOOooOOOoo, because it's the only key on his keyboard that works.

Soul2.desc_line1: Fat chonker this one is! It must be the moonmoon diet these ghosts have, they should start eating some of those fruits for a change!

Soul3.desc_line1: It's smiling as if it knows something that you don't...

Soul4.desc_line1: Well, his mom did warn him if that he kept making funny faces that it'd freeze that way!

Soul5.desc_line1: Don't judge it, you'd be mad too if someone squished YOU into that weirdo lookin' pattern!

Soul6.desc_line1: He be oozin' and cruisin' and ain't worried 'bout nothin'

TreeInterior1b.desc_line1: Made of circle that's been carved into the shape of a wood.            NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Branches

TreeInterior2.desc_line1: Every time I plant one of these, someone eventually steals it and puts a fully grown tree in its place! Very annoying!

BabaYagaETC.desc_line1: Eventually you'll be able to turn these into a hatchable egg! Or maybe you already can! Or maybe you never will! Who knows what future content there may be!

DesertA1.desc_line1: This sand aint right, I tell you hwat!

DesertA1b.desc_line1: The result of letting heat and sand get it on if you know what I'm sayin.                        NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Sandy Pots

DesertA2.desc_line1: Wait a minute, this isn't a real megalodon tooth!

DesertA3.desc_line1: You could probably start a restaurant selling these! Just employ an overeager cook, give the place a cool name like The Crispy Crustacean, and you'd be set!

DesertA3b.desc_line1: Ohhhhh, that's what people mean when they say Love At First Sight!                             NOTE: This is a very rare drop from Crabcakes

DesertB1.desc_line1: How many O's are in this item's name? Yep, you're right, there's six! Good job!

DesertB2.desc_line1: It's an American Flag with red paint spilled on all the non-red bits... no wait, it's the German Flag, but they ran out of black and yellow material.

DesertB3.desc_line1: That looks sharp! Is probably what the pincermin said before you cut his arm off.

DesertC2b.desc_line1: In case you haven't noticed, these are all references to the famous early 90s videogame called Gex! This description is like a bad joke at Louis CK's house!

DesertC3.desc_line1: It's like a monocle, but not quite.

DesertC4.desc_line1: The very tippy top of the shell, with some of the underneath part attached as well.

SnowA1.desc_line1: A ball of sheep wool. Well, it used to be a ball of ice cream but then I re-drew it.

SnowA2.desc_line1: Eugh whats this WATER doing around my ice???

SnowA2a.desc_line1: Mmm yellow, my favorite flavor of snow!

SnowA3.desc_line1: Sad times I hope I remember to change this before relase.

SnowA4.desc_line1: It's got a horn stuck in it. I guess you could say this wool is kinda

SnowB2.desc_line1: No see, this is a mamOOth tusk, not a mammoth tusk, thats why you think it looks weird. Trust me, it's an incredibly drawn mamooth tusk, truly a work of art.

SnowB2a.desc_line1: The thrilling documentary that captures the first three years of Jonathan Ice's life, from birth to preschool. It also has thousands of 1 Star Ratings online claiming it's false advertising.

SnowB5.desc_line1: If you have two of these together, please be careful what other objects you put near them, I need to keep this game age appropriate!

SnowB3.desc_line1: Click the pen on, then hold it down against your desk and let go, and BAM that baby will fly you straight to the principal's office!

SnowB4.desc_line1: Ah Mr. Thermostat, not looking so hot now that I've broken you into tiny little bits... no seriously, I can't tell the temperature now that you're broken.

SnowC1.desc_line1: This vacuum operated liquid transfer system is capable of dispencing over 500 mL of dangerous dihydrogen monoxide chemical compounds from one end to the other!

SnowC2.desc_line1: Wow this is just a cheap recolouring of the normal snakeskin! I want my money back!

SnowC3.desc_line1: Uhhhh... which one which one...?? The red or the blue??? Cmon think think think.. Blue...? 'BOOOOOM'.       Wait, this is an audio cord description? Whoops, I thought this was the Bomb Defuser description!!

SnowC4.desc_line1: It's the only transparent item in IdleOn! If they weren't, they'd just be pirate eyepatches after all...

SnowC4a.desc_line1: Why yes, I have also played that game for 100s of hours since it released over 10 years ago!

SnowC5.desc_line1: Wait a minute, these are just regular bones painted red! Wait another minute, no, that's actual blood... ew.

GalaxyA1.desc_line1: According to herblore books, this purple cap is sterile. Those purple fungi that grow from the ground, however, will mutate if exposed to toxic oil radiation.

GalaxyA2.desc_line1: Oh, THATS where he put the remote, all the way out here in outer space thousands of miles from the surface! Oh that silly man!

GalaxyA2b.desc_line1: Oh, THATS why the remote wasn't working when I pushed the buttons, the batteries were all the way out here in the rare drop table!

GalaxyA3.desc_line1: WAIT NO STOP! Don't eat the rest of this donut! Think about it... if it was really worth eating, why was it left like this, all un-eaten and such? Think before you eat!

GalaxyA4.desc_line1: Rub it, maybe a genie will come out! Oh wait, you already killed the genie. Maybe try 'not murder' next time.

GalaxyB1.desc_line1: With the main prey of the Soda Can being the Soda Bottle, one can conclude that bottle caps are indigestible, and will remain untarnished after being consumed.

GalaxyB3.desc_line1: The tongue is wrapped around the bone.

GalaxyB4.desc_line1: Yo... yuhhh, yea, yea. They said I was doomed from the start, maaan ain't no wrapper made it past the worst part...

GalaxyB5.desc_line1: I wonder if this one's an undercover agent too...

GalaxyC1.desc_line1: It's a lame shell that's been desaturated due to it's unimportance.

GalaxyC1b.desc_line1: Yow wow wow! This one's got a pearl in it!!

GalaxyC2.desc_line1: It's like some sort of tentankle ball. Hang on, let me try that again. It's like some sort of tentacle ball.

GalaxyC4.desc_line1: ...37 Megawatts of electricity, if my voltmeter reading is correct!

Quest17.desc_line1: A piece of rock from the big bad wolf himself. Careful, it's overflowing with green plasma energy! No wait, that's just some moss.

Quest29.desc_line1: A piece of rock from the bigger badder wolf himself. Careful, it's overflowing with poisonous ooze! No wait, that's just plasma energy...

EfauntDrop1.desc_line1: A piece of Efaunt's tunic. I guess it must have gotten torn off while you were absolutely obliterating them with big time Damage.

EfauntDrop2.desc_line1: Chaotic Efaunt is probably glad you removed a few of his ribs, for uhh... various reasons.

Chiz0.desc_line1: A spike from Chizoar's neck. It's ice cold, and sharp as a tack.

Chiz1.desc_line1: A spike from Chaotic Chizoar's neck. Despite it being made of ice, it burns at the touch due to its acidity.

TrollPart.desc_line1: Even the scales look like they have a wry smile, almost as if it remembers the part it played in that infamous tutorial prank you were unfortunately involved in

KrukPart.desc_line1: Extracted straight from the horses mouth! At least I think he was a horse... maybe a buffalo? It came from a mouth at the very least.

KrukPart2.desc_line1: I guess proper dental hygiene isn't one of the requirements to becoming a Divinity.

LavaA1.desc_line1: Poor suggma slug, couldn't even handle a little bit of water eh?

LavaA1b.desc_line1: Huh... was uh... was that one some sort of king or something? This species really needs to sort out its heirarchy, it didn't look any different from the others!

LavaA2.desc_line1: Look if you're gonna kill the poor thing, you may as well have the decency of finishing the whole thing!

LavaA3.desc_line1: Reduced to mere glass fragments... I guess thats just the price he pays for being a monster, his destiny was calling.

LavaA4.desc_line1: Thats not your cheese! Err, thats nacho cheese! Ok wow that really doesn't work typed out like that...

LavaA5.desc_line1: It's got a built in gyroscope to help with balance. Unfortunately, it isn't turned on.

LavaB1.desc_line1: It's like a meatball served in tomato sauce... lets eat!

LavaB2.desc_line1: So, is this pile of crumbs still 1 skull, or like a thousand skulls? At what point when crumbling does a skull stop being a skull?

LavaB3.desc_line1: So this is where all those Youth Sports get their half time snacks!

LavaB5.desc_line1: Ew, that's basically its saliva! Why are you keeping it in your inventory?? Ugh whatever...

LavaC1.desc_line1: Where are the green eggs to go with these?

ClassSwapB.desc_line1: Hold down on this item to change elite class within your class. Divine Knight to Blood Berserker, Beast Master to Siege Breaker, etc.

ResetBox.desc_line1: Hold down to reset all post office upgrades made on this character! You'll get all the Box Points refunded of course, no problemo!

Ht.desc_line1: Drag this onto any normal hat to turn it into a premium hat! Doing so will wipe all it's stats, and give it {1 all stat and 5 Premium Upgrade Slots, just like any other premium hat.

StonePremRestore.desc_line1: Drag this onto any Premium Hat to refund all Premium Stones used on it. You must have at least 4 open inventory spaces to use this btw

StonePremStatswap.desc_line1: Put this stone in your inventory, with 2 premium hats to its left and right. Then hold down on the stone to swap their special bonuses! Also works with regular hats made premium by the Hat Premiumifier

SmithingHammerChisel3.desc_line1: Drop this on the statue man, and you'll turn him to onyx and unlock the ability to trade in statues for Onyx rank!

BobJoePickle.desc_line1: He was one of the good ones...
BobJoePickle.desc_line2: Alas he is now just a pickle.
BobJoePickle.desc_line3: Good for scaring a cat though!

BallJoePickle.desc_line1: What have they done to ya BobJoe?

Quest1.desc_line1: It's proof that you can mine, and
Quest1.desc_line2: it's even signed by Glumlee himself!

Crystal3.desc_line1: Restores power to the Galaxy Portal in the glacier town, allowing travel to World 4!

Crystal4.desc_line1: Restores power to the Magma Portal in the galaxy town, allowing travel to World 5!

PeanutS.desc_line1: It's like a regular peanut, except
PeanutS.desc_line2: it's made of stone instead of pea.
PeanutS.desc_line3: I bet a Rocklyte would enjoy it!

Quest3.desc_line1: A tiny ketchup bottle, small enough
Quest3.desc_line2: for a Frog to use. Would go

Quest4.desc_line1: A tiny mustard bottle, small enough
Quest4.desc_line2: for a Frog to never use because
Quest4.desc_line3: mustard is gross. Would go great

Mayo.desc_line1: Why did someone bury a bottle of mayo? Wait... why did you go dig it up??

Trash2.desc_line1: Its all hard and crusty now.

Trash3.desc_line1: It's a bullet, and it's got your name on it!

Quest5.desc_line1: It's a fake jar filled with springs!
Quest5.desc_line2: The best way to crack a joke with

Quest6.desc_line1: It says a Giant Wolf-like Golem was
Quest6.desc_line2: seen walking with the gem even

Quest7.desc_line1: Looks like the piece of a golem.
Quest7.desc_line3: engraved on the side of it.

Quest10.desc_line1: You're playing a game right now
Quest10.desc_line2: with a sub-plot that involves a
Quest10.desc_line3: jar of sand falling in love with
Quest10.desc_line4: a cup of tea. Just thought I'd

Quest11.desc_line2: to have a negative crafting level.

Quest12.desc_line1: Dog Bone must have died from a blunt strike to the head, surely that's where he got his Ghost-Name from! Pretty proud of myself for solving this, even if Item Descriptions like me aren't capable of feeling pride!

Quest13.desc_line1: An empty box, the perfect place to put all your Hermit Cans, Megalodon teeth, and pure water... that you don't have anymore haha!

Quest14.desc_line1: Wait a minute, these stats have misleading Y-axes and invalid sampling methods! Even then, they show no clear evidence for rats stealing jobs! How could anyone possibly believe this data?

Quest15.desc_line1: Sprout's red frisbee! I hope you didn't get shrunken down by a magic apple on your way up, or your stetchy dog brother might laugh at you!

Quest16.desc_line1: The guy who carelessly dropped this microphone is a moron, and that's a fact. Boom, mic drop... ah crap.

Quest18.desc_line1: A key to a door, but there are still more! Why so many? They were on sale for a penny!

Quest19.desc_line1: Avast, land lubber! This coin be property of the YumYum Sea Pirates! Ye best be returning it, lest ye want an underwater funeral, arg!

Quest20.desc_line1: That's weird, Bandit Bob's signature looks an awful lot like yours...

Quest21.desc_line1: Yea yea I know, this quest doesn't really make sense. Although, if you reeeaaally think about it, you'll realize that it still makes no sense... so it's best not to think about it!

Quest22.desc_line1: Represents a single subscriber on the Corporatube Video Platform. It You'sed to be called something else, but no one around here remembers.

Quest23.desc_line1: Represents a single follower on Instablab, who probably sound like this: 'Oh mah gawd Becky, you would not Buh Leeeeve how lame this game I'm playing is. They have a joke about Insta that tooootally isn't funnay, like seriouslayy!

Quest24.desc_line1: Represents a single follower on Cloudsound. This isn't a website, it's literally a giant cloud that emits sound that people enjoy following around. Why, what were YOU thinking this was?

Quest25.desc_line1: Hold down to read the card! There's a 1 in 75 chance it contains a Birthday Hat recipe, and a 74 in 75 chance it contains a few dollars from grandma.

Quest26.desc_line1: The traditional gift given to those about to be victimized. A favorite amongst criminals!

Quest27.desc_line1: Mmmmm, these nuts are so yuuuummy!

Quest28.desc_line1: Mere mortal, your meager intellect doesn't leave you with enough patience! Wait until powers even greater than myself allow me to drop the crystal to World 6. The time will come, I assure you.

GoldricP1.desc_line1: It's a painting of a strangely out of place gold bar fellow. They look nervous underneath their outward bravado.

GoldricP2.desc_line1: It's a rendition of the Battle of Sassasge, wherein Goldrichius Von Gallbladder waged war on the municipal kingdom of Sterling S. Elvar

GoldricP3.desc_line1: The victory portrait of King Goldrichius Sr. after successfully dethroning S.S. Elvar from the East Yum-Yum dunedaries.

Quest30.desc_line1: Hold down to open! There's a santa hat in one of these, as well as various holiday exclusive goodies, even cards!

Quest31.desc_line1: Did you like those 20 gems you just picked up? Well you'll LOVE the 500 gems I just added to your account. This paper is worthless btw lol it's just a picture of a gem.

Cutter.desc_line1: I bet if you dropped these on a sewer grating, it would snap the bars right off!

Quest32.desc_line1: 'I literally just die over and over, I can't even fight back other than just running into them. Honestly I wish I was dead, but even then I just keep respawning, literally the worst experience ever, 1 star!!'

Quest33.desc_line1: 'WTF y do my items CONSTANTLY DISAPPEAR I HATE IT!! Complete RUBBISH! 1 STAR UNTIL YOU FIX MY SPECIFIC PROBLEM and even then I'll probably just raise it to 2 stars lol'

Quest34.desc_line1: 'This is NOT an Idle game! I actually have to play it sometimes! And why are there actual pictures on the screen, instead of just words and text boxes?? I can't believe I paid 0 dollars for this trash!'

Quest35.desc_line1: I remember when I was a kid, I spent an HOUR making a GLASS container look like it was a little friend using googley eyes just like these! If only there was a CONTAINER in this game, so you could do it to!

Quest36.desc_line1: Blinks repeatedly when close to the Black Market, where you buy the Ankh used in the ice zone to get the Hedjet... wait, wrong game, sorry!

Quest37.desc_line1: An old lady pawned it off to the bazaar claiming it was some 'ancient artifact of the pharoah King Doot'. It's probably just scrap metal, doubt it's even real silver. Would make for a decent Necklace!

Quest38.desc_line1: Hold down to open! Contains a random cool-kid item, like gems, exp balloons, or even time candy! Also, 1 in every 500 gifts contains the 'Ultra Unboxer' Trophy!

Quest39.desc_line1: Hold down on a letter to spawn a Valentslime, or turn these in each day to the Loveulyte for a reward!

Quest40.desc_line1: Hold down to open a random reward like Gems and Cards! There's a 1 in 700 chance for a special ROSE CAPE, and there are 3 different roses! Also if you're unlucky, you're GUARANTEED to get a rose every 650 boxes!

Quest41.desc_line1: Curse you flowey! I trusted you, I accepted your pellets of friendship, and then you had to go and throw it all away! And now here you are, trying to take over yet another video game... well I NOT GONNA LE-- oh wait, these are just normal flowers

Quest42.desc_line1: Hold down to open for a random reward! Or, hold down for a LONG time to open them faster... yea, dreams do come true #

Quest43.desc_line1: Hold down to summon a friendly easter monster. But be careful, unlike real life where all friends are genuine, these monsters are just pretending to be your friend for personal gain!

Quest44.desc_line1: Hold down to summon a mini boss or a green mushroom. It's a 50 50 shot which one you get!

Quest45.desc_line1: The key to Bandit Bob's Party Dungeon! No not that dungeon... you're thinking of Snakenhotep's Dungeon, this one's for Bandit Bob's dungeon. So yea, this is worthless.

Quest46.desc_line1: A great behemoth has emerged from its slumber... and it now roams the fishing minigame! If you catch 2 whales, then purposefully avoid catching the 3rd whale, the ocean behemoth will eventually appear! Catch it to win a trophy!

Quest47.desc_line1: It has a very peculiar stench... the smell is so unbearable, your damage is lowered by 50% and your Max HP is just 1! Only the sands of a dead Biggie Hours Miniboss could reverse the aging this peanut has undergone!

Quest48.desc_line1: Now that's a happy looking peanut! I wish he was MY best friend, but no one wants to be friends with sentient item dialogue ^

Quest49.desc_line1: Hold down to open for a random reward! Or, hold down for a LONG time to open them faster.

Quest50.desc_line1: Hold down to summon a bunch of Summer Monsters, and get a random Pearl!

Pearl4.desc_line1: Hold down to gain 20% EXP in the skill that's shown in the corner of the screen. If you're in a town, you will gain EXP in the town skill. Only works on skills below level 30.

Pearl5.desc_line1: Hold down to gain Class EXP. The amount you gain is based on your Class LV.

Pearl6.desc_line1: Hold down to gain 40% EXP in the skill that's shown in the corner of the screen. If you're in a town, you will gain EXP in the town skill. Only works on skills below level 50.

Quest56.desc_line1: Hold down on this vintage Dootophone to active all the obelisks on Doot's burial platform at once!

Quest57.desc_line1: Hold down on this cog to turn it into a Refurbished Cog, IF you have a construction LV of 75{.

Quest58.desc_line1: Made from a Damaged Cog, which you can buy at the Town Shop!

Quest59.desc_line1: A slip of paper indicating that a Ms. Shuvelle La Deuge intends to vote for Mayor Hoggindaz

Quest60.desc_line1: A slip of paper indicating that a Sir Yondergreen Von Timberbottom intends to vote for Mayor Hoggindaz

Quest61.desc_line1: A slip of paper indicating that a Mr. Bill Brr doesn't intend to vote for any of these political puppets, but he left it blank so you filled it in for Hoggi.

Quest62.desc_line1: It's the last will and testament of some penguin monster. Just pretend you signed it, ol' Yondergreen seems a little blind and probably wont notice.

Quest64.desc_line1: Hold to open! Contains a random Giftmas goodie, from event cards to foods!

Quest65.desc_line1: Collect 3 of these, then hold down on the stack of 3 to unlock the Chip Repository!

Quest66.desc_line1: Collect 7 of these, then hold down on the stack of 7 to unlock the Jewel Spinner!

Quest67.desc_line1: Buy this once and hold down on it to permanently allow for free teleports inbetween World Towns without consuming a teleport! From town to town, free of charge!

Whetstone.desc_line1: Hold down on this item to completely reset your spent Anvil Points for this character.

Quest68.desc_line1: Drop this on the snowy pile in the Refigeration Station in World 3. There are rumors that the recent snowfall will coagulate with the slush in horrible ways...

Quest69.desc_line1: It may be a skull, but it sure ain't no Killroy!

Quest70.desc_line1: IdleOn is out on iOS devices! The Rift Ripper must have kept a few of these back when he played during the iOS Launch event... Hold down to open, and a random reward will drop at your feet!

Quest71.desc_line1: Contains a random number of gems, hold down to open! It could be just a couple gems, but it could also have as many as 10,000 gems!

Quest74.desc_line1: You shouldn't be reading this... unless it's like on the Wiki or something, then yea I ain't pointin' no fingers or nothing.

Quest75.desc_line1: Hold to open! Contains a random Spring Event goodie, from event cards to foods! ALSO, if you open a total of 500 Baggies, you'll get a limited edition Spring event NAMETAG!

Quest76.desc_line1: Hold down to change your daily reset time by 15 minutes. If this item is on the left side of the inventory, it'll DECREASE by 15 minutes. If it is on the right side, it'll INCREASE by 15 minutes.

Quest77.desc_line1: Hold down to fast forward a day, restocking shops and triggering various daily rewards and systems.

EquipmentStatues8.desc_line1: I don't think the sculptor who named this statue back in 3000 BC would be happy with how his typo would be interpreted.

EquipmentStatues9.desc_line1: What's that, statue? You want to... take me by the hand and lead me to the land? With that land pecifically being the one that you understand?

EquipmentStatues10.desc_line1: It takes a true artist to make a realistic statue like this one. He captured the flying aspect of those stone flies perfectly!

EquipmentStatues11.desc_line1: I haven't read a book since middle school, so I'm just assuming this is what they look like.

EquipmentStatues12.desc_line1: A little monument to the efforts of a most devious coyote, whose dreams were always just out of reach, and whose head often felt the crushing blow of defeat.

EquipmentStatues13.desc_line1: They used to tie women to these things and throw them into the ocean to see if they were a witch. If they were, they'd use all the water in the ocean to upgrade the cauldron and thus not drown! Not sure what happened if they werent.

EquipmentStatues14.desc_line1: This statue is beautiful! Well, at least to me.

EquipmentStatues15.desc_line1: This statue was created by shooting a target statue into a stationary arrow statue.

EquipmentStatues16.desc_line1: It's more of an open container than a box, really.

EquipmentStatues18.desc_line1: The sculptor got so fed up with people misinterpreting his previous statues, he felt the need to spell this one out.

EquipmentStatues19.desc_line1: The end result of someone trying to cut a slab in half with a ceramic saw, and then leaving early after they saw me watching them in the bushes, writing down what they were doing in this description.

EquipmentStatues20.desc_line1: This statue gonna make u heckin rich!

EquipmentStatues21.desc_line1: This statue makes me really hungry... but for some reason it inspires me to cook rather than giving higher food bonuses.

EquipmentStatues22.desc_line1: This statue somehow boosts the effectiveness of pets getting it on...

EquipmentStatues23.desc_line1: This statue makes you do more damage. Nothing fancy.

EquipmentStatues24.desc_line1: This statue will bring you closer to god. Or gods in this case, the world of IdleOn is polytheistic!

EquipmentStatues25.desc_line1: This statue does not actually function as a boat, and will sink as youd expect a large piece of stone would.
